
Elastic Runtime defines one default ASG, `default_security_group`. This group allows all outbound traffic from application containers on public and private networks except for the link-local range, `169.254.0.0/16`.

The ASG is defined in the Cloud Controller configuration like this:

<pre>
security_group_definitions:
- name: default_security_group
  rules:
  - protocol: all
    destination: 0.0.0.0-169.253.255.255
  - protocol: all
    destination: 169.255.0.0-255.255.255.255
</pre>

Pivotal recommends that Elastic Runtime  administrators modify the default ASGs so that outbound network traffic cannot access internal components.